{
  "stem": "18102.3",
  "chunk_idx": 6,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 11.1,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "And suddenly things changed and this time for good, because Stalin and the Russians decided to take over not just Vilna, but all of Lithuania, declaring war or whatever.",
      "word_count": 29
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "[SIGHS] At that time I didn't know what it was.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "It was explained again to my father.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "And this meant, now, that my father would become, again, a refugee, because he would have to run and leave us.",
      "word_count": 21
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 13,
      "text": "The reason was obvious.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 14,
      "text": "He had correctly fled-- not returned to the Russians.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 15,
      "text": "Certainly he wasn't going to fall into their trap and be found here in Vilna, because the same fate would await him.",
      "word_count": 22
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 16,
      "text": "So he left.",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 17,
      "text": "And we were again-- the fear factor returned, because now we were always afraid that someone would come searching for him.",
      "word_count": 21
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 18,
      "text": "And my mother would use a signal.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 19,
      "text": "She would hang a, a, a towel over the rail in, in the window in the veranda.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 20,
      "text": "If the towel was hanging there, that meant that my father could come and visit us.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 21,
      "text": "If the towel wasn't there, that meant that it was dangerous for him to come.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 22,
      "text": "And we lived in this fashion, with fear, for another-- nearly a year.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 23,
      "text": "[PAUSES FOR 4 SECONDS] It was at this point that I later learned that my father applied for a visa to Japan.",
      "word_count": 22
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 24,
      "text": "Because by getting a visa, it meant you could ask for permission to leave Russia, leave Russian rule.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 25,
      "text": "If you didn't have any place to go, then you would not be able to apply.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 26,
      "text": "But if you had a visa, you could then apply.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 27,
      "text": "That's the issue of Sugihara, the Polish-- the-- sorry, the Japanese ambassador to Lithuania that gave out thousands of visas to Jews and saved their lives by doing so, because they were able to leave Lithuania-- Russia.",
      "word_count": 37
    }
  ],
